  "time_ut": 1661497870,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0ddc\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dc5\u0dda \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0db8\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca \u0da7\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca 1000\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d89\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dad\u0dd4\u0dc5 \u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0da7\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "1000 metric tons of free urea to this country in the next fortnight",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The World Food and Agriculture Organization has agreed to provide 375,000 50 kg bags of urea fertilizer to low-income farming families in Sri Lanka for rice cultivation.",
        "This stock of urea fertilizer is to be given free of charge to 375,000 farmers who have less than an acre of paddy at the rate of 50 kg per farmer.",
        "Agriculture Minister Mahinda Amaraweera agreed to provide urea fertilizer for the high season as per a discussion held with officials of the World Food and Agriculture Organization.",
        "The Minister of Agriculture said that our country will receive 1000 metric tons as its first stock in the next two weeks.",
        "Yesterday (25) the Minister held a discussion with small, medium and large scale mill owners regarding the purchase of paddy in the spring season and cultivation activities in the high season. He also discussed about providing urea fertilizer for the high season.",
        "Rice mill owners said that the farmers say that the urea fertilizer provided by the government in the yala season is 100 percent of high quality. Therefore, they said, the paddy yield in the yala season will exceed the expected level. It was planned to cultivate about 275,000 hectares of paddy this year, but with the government's decision to provide urea fertilizer, the amount of paddy cultivated has now increased to 512,000 hectares.",
        "Meanwhile, the World Food and Agriculture Organization has also decided to provide a subsidy of 18,000 rupees per family to 14 lakh families to grow mung beans with the aim of increasing the nutrition of women-led low-income families.",
        "Thus, in order to popularize mung bean cultivation in Anuradhapura, Polonnaruwa, Monaragala, Ampara and Hambantota districts, the women of those districts have decided to give the money subsidy to the basic farming families.",
        "The Secretary of the Ministry Mr. Rohana Pushpakumara and many small, medium and large scale paddy mill owners participated in this discussion."
      ],
